<script lang="ts">
import { toast } from "varsel";

const variantOptions = ["default", "success", "warning", "destructive"] as const;

const triggerVariant = (variant: (typeof variantOptions)[number]) =>
	toast({
		title: `${variant} toast`,
		description: "Pick the tone that matches the event.",
		variant,
	});
</script>

# Variants & styling

Varsel keeps visuals opinionated yet flexible. Choose a preset variant for status-driven colors and stack your own classes on top for bespoke experiences.

## Variant property

Set the `variant` property when invoking `toast`. Available values are `default`, `success`, `warning` and `destructive`.

```svelte
<script lang="ts">
	import { toast } from "varsel";

	const variants = ["default", "success", "warning", "destructive"] as const;
</script>

<div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
	{#each variants as variant}
		<button
			class="rounded-md bg-card border border-border h-9 px-4 py-2 text-sm font-medium text-foreground hover:bg-card-muted shadow-sm transition-[background-color,scale] duration-150 ease-out active:scale-[0.975]"
			onclick={() =>
				toast({
					title: `${variant} toast`,
					description: "Pick the tone that matches the event.",
					variant,
				})}
		>
			{variant}
		</button>
	{/each}
</div>
```

